{
  "definitions": [
    {
      "primitive": {
        "isPure": true,
        "isTotal": true,
        "metadata": {
          "comments": [
            "compare(x, y) returns the hydra.util.Comparison value that classifies the relationship between x and y under the type's ordering: LessThan if x < y, EqualTo if x == y, GreaterThan if x > y. The result type's three-valued tag is the canonical primitive comparison; the boolean comparators (lt/lte/gt/gte) and equal are derivable from it. Requires an 'ordering' type-class constraint on the argument type, which is the closest Hydra equivalent to Haskell's Ord instance. Total. Corresponds to Haskell's compare :: Ord a => a -> a -> Ordering."],
          "description": "Compare two values and return a Comparison.",
          "seeAlso": []},
        "name": "hydra.lib.equality.compare",
        "signature": {
          "parameters": [
            {"isLazy": false, "name": "arg0", "type": {"variable": "x"}},
            {"isLazy": false, "name": "arg1", "type": {"variable": "x"}}],
          "result": {"type": {"variable": "hydra.util.Comparison"}},
          "typeParameters": [{"constraints": [{"simple": "ordering"}], "name": "x"}]}}},
    {
      "primitive": {
        "isPure": true,
        "isTotal": true,
        "metadata": {
          "comments": [
            "equal(x, y) returns true if x and y are structurally equal under the type's notion of equality. Requires an 'equality' type-class constraint on the argument type, which is the closest Hydra equivalent to Haskell's Eq instance. Equality is reflexive, symmetric, and transitive (no NaN-style exception on floating-point: floating-point equality is provided per the underlying host's IEEE 754 comparison rules, so NaN /= NaN at the level of float64/float32). Total. Corresponds to Haskell's (==) :: Eq a => a -> a -> Bool."],
          "description": "Check whether two values are equal.",
          "seeAlso": []},
        "name": "hydra.lib.equality.equal",
        "signature": {
          "parameters": [
            {"isLazy": false, "name": "arg0", "type": {"variable": "x"}},
            {"isLazy": false, "name": "arg1", "type": {"variable": "x"}}],
          "result": {"type": {"literal": {"boolean": {}}}},
          "typeParameters": [{"constraints": [{"simple": "equality"}], "name": "x"}]}}},
    {
      "primitive": {
        "isPure": true,
        "isTotal": true,
        "metadata": {
          "comments": [
            "gt(x, y) returns true iff x > y under the type's ordering. Requires an 'ordering' constraint on the argument type. Total. Corresponds to Haskell's (>) :: Ord a => a -> a -> Bool."],
          "description": "Check whether the first value is greater than the second.",
          "seeAlso": []},
        "name": "hydra.lib.equality.gt",
        "signature": {
          "parameters": [
            {"isLazy": false, "name": "arg0", "type": {"variable": "x"}},
